title: New Jerusalem stabbing attack wounds two Israelis: Police, medics - Region - World
text:
Related Palestinian shot by Israeli police in east Jerusalem dies: Officials Palestinian killed by Israeli forces in Jerusalem clashes: Medics Netanyahu moves to lower tensions over Jerusalem holy site White House condemns violence in West Bank, Jerusalem A new stabbing in Jerusalem wounded two Israelis on Saturday in the latest in a wave of such attacks that have spread fear among residents, police and medics said.
Police said the attacker had been "neutralised" without providing further details on whether the suspect had been captured of killed. They referred to the attacker as a "terrorist."
